The teenager had been standing outside a house at Gill Marcus when someone shot at him in the early hours of Saturday morning. CAPE TOWN - Police in the Eastern Cape are investigating the murder of a 15-year old boy in the town of Humansdorp. The teenager had been standing outside a house at Gill Marcus when someone shot at him in the early hours of Saturday morning. According to police, he sustained several gunshot wounds. “Police are investigating a case of murder after the 15-year old, Antonio Botha, was fatally wounded at about 02:00 this morning,” said police spokesperson Captain Gerda Swart. Community members heard the shots and rushed to his aid, calling police and paramedics.